ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Over the past 30 days, have you had any caffeinated or 'decaf' drinks such as coffee, energy drinks, tea, or soda?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Over the past 30 days, on an average day, how many caffeinated drinks do you have?
Notes: Number of drinks per day; -7 =N/A; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Over the past 30 days, on an average day, what size are these caffeinated drinks?
Notes: 1 = Small (<8 oz); 2 = Medium (8-12 oz); 3 = Large (>12oz); -7 = N/A; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: How often did you drink the beverage? - Decaffeinated coffee (Instant and brewed)
Notes: 0 = Never or less than once per month; 1 = 1 to 3 per month; 2 = 1 per week; 3 = 2 to 4 per week; 4 = 5 to 6 per week; 5 = 1 per day; 6 = 2 to 3 per day; 7 = 4 to 5 per day; 8 = 6 or more per day
